<TITLE> Tigers make bright start </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Old Trafford, Jun 4 (bdnews24.com)-- England were 83 for 3 after choosing to bat first against Bangladesh in the second and final test at Old Trafford on Friday. Spinner Abdur Razzak got a wicket with the first ball of the tour when Alastair Cook got a thick edge to Junaed Siddique at first slip for 29. Earlier, a double strike from Shafiul Islam left the hosts at 48 for two. Captain Andrew Stauss (21) edged him to Imrul Kayes at second slip and then Jonathan Trottt (3) played a delivery on to the top of his stumps. Bangladesh made two changes to the team that played the Lord's Test. Robiul Islam, who made his debut in that match, has been replaced by Shafiul Islam, who played against England during the winter tour in Bangladesh. Abdur Razzak has been drafted in as the extra spinner in an attempt to exploit the extra turn and bounce. Yorkshire seamer Ajmal Shahzad made his Test debut in place of the injured Tim Bresnan, after he was picked ahead of left-armer Ryan Sidebo
